{"type": "article", "id": 38891, "title": "有了这条胶带，用乐高装修房子再不是事儿｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-03-16T23:25:23Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 29, "name": "Top 15"}, {"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 536, "name": "三星"}, {"id": 9226, "name": "Yves Béhar"}, {"id": 27294, "name": "Federico Babina"}, {"id": 38621, "name": "Lorenzo Rocco"}, {"id": 38622, "name": "Lucia Litman"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 8, "praise_count": 180, "image": "img/article/article_show/20170316195750ACqx8o3RvXUmerYg.jpg", "contents": "<p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Nimuno Loops by Nimuno</h3><p>除了平坦的桌面，你有想过在转角或是玻璃窗上拼乐高吗？为了让积木爱好者不受拘束地进行创作，设计工作室 Nimuno 决定将积木和胶带的概念融合在一起。除了造型之外，这款名为 Nimuno Loops 的积木用胶带和我们平时使用的双面胶没有太大区别，可以随意弯曲、裁剪，使用时只要撕下背贴即可。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/nimuno-loops-the-toy-block-tape#/\">链接</a>参与众筹，售价从 11 美元起，每盒包含两卷一米长的胶带。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195811QjBMIrK1yZuaeYOp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.361111\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195810JjC6WT1rcLIloRXH.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195811P8at96vqlkZQBXYL.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.332813\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703161958137Ow4YRZhFf9JTb8e.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.331250\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195819cP6zK87DlxqnRQyT.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.392188\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>MUSICON</h3><p>为了让小朋友们可以一次体验到多种乐器的乐趣，美国一群热爱音乐的设计师们推出了一款名为 MUSICON 的多功能乐器。它的主体是一个表面布满圆形按钮的滚筒，最上方是一排依靠磁力吸附的可拆卸乐器部件。虽然看起来有些复杂，但用它创作乐曲其实非常简单：推动一旁的控制杆设定速度之后，按下后凸起的按钮在通过上方的乐器时就会因碰撞发出声响。小朋友们既可以直接通过简单的按压学习作曲，也可以将上方的乐器拆下来配合玩具演奏。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/kamillaszuk/musicon-composing-and-coding-for-ages-3-and-up\">众筹链接</a>，最低价为 2499 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703161959105n8ITeRYojsxDuPU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.582353\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195909Uc0efsW36By1NPln.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.588235\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195911CXRZeDHM96wxoLBG.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.433824\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195912uM1k4ctRPi3jTI0F.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.423529\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195911lDF3HgS9r2Kqhtyv.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.530882\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195910swgiOmECNI2Wv6eZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.841176\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>The Frame by Yves Béhar</h3><p>一台黑漆漆的电视放在家里总觉得和环境有些格格不入？瑞士知名设计师 <a href=\"https://fuseproject.com/\">Yves Béhar</a> 与<a href=\"http://www.samsung.com/us/\">三星</a>联手打造的 The Frame 想改变这一现状，让电视也能拥有艺术装饰品的属性。当你关闭 The Frame 时，它不会像常见的电视那样变成一块黑色的屏幕，而是进入一个被称为 Art Mode 的虚拟美术馆，展示来自世界各地的画作。为了节约能源，内置的传感器会确保 The Frame 在无人的状态下停止展示。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195933SHqdL14QVY93jBgW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195933dcjGMawhOkHtSrmD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703161959347p8egE2LnoMXfcht.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749389\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195934Qd89cYTtgz5Hl2qe.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749389\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316195933kjBRohAPMiuz8fxc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.200489\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Erre by Lorenzo Rocco</h3><p>为了让 DJ Erre 的出道 CD 能够脱颖而出， 负责品牌设计的 <a href=\"https://lorenzorocco.myportfolio.com/\">Lorenzo Rocco</a> 选择了名字中重复的字母 R 作为主要的视觉元素，设计了一个由斜线和圆弧构成的 logo，看起来简洁有力，同时又能让人联想到不断旋转播放的黑胶唱片。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200211ZEsFr2P9I1uKpTiJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.599286\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"medium-insert-image-active\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"medium-insert-caption-placeholder\"></figcaption></figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200211PN7EoglBVWJRcDFq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.599286\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200211VMY081TS5IejRNzx.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.599286\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200211yFTV1tSmnpJwdkfs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.599286\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703162002135ZGkBaWgOjK7fY1p.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.599286\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Pantone Posts by Lucia Litman</h3><p>现居旧金山的 <a href=\"http://www.lucialitman.com/\">Lucia Litman</a> 自称是一名业余摄影师兼食品造型师，热爱食物和设计的她以潘通的色卡为灵感，从日常生活中寻找颜色的食物搭配成有趣的摄影作品，就像是一本食物界的色彩指南。如果你喜欢这些美味的色卡，可以关注 Litman 的 <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/lucialitman/\">Instagram</a>。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703162001212xgHnk3KGhlr0oiZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200121KMfHI02akZosvV4F.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200122xbuQ5SiUsCGOIL9P.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200121JsYyznOt5WXTg1UK.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200122mFu8yafU029DwXlY.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Archiatric by Federico Babina</h3><p>还记得那个喜欢用建筑讲故事的意大利插画家 <a href=\"http://federicobabina.com/\">Federico Babina</a> 吗？在新作 Archiatri 中，Babina 用稀奇古怪的建筑表现了一系列困扰着人们的精神疾病，比如痴呆、恐惧、焦虑和强迫症等。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703162000559Jaj4UAiqYQkBhDS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703162000561q3n5kHptsKlhzOu.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200056ziWLh3HMZqVaS4bX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200056O63BXz5vhmPtbFGI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200056YwJtLFXrREGifuN1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170316200056teMiqLAQ21x3Ysrh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}